Norilsk, Polymetal, Gazprom Neft: Russian Equities Preview

-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 
2011-08-10T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/norilsk-polymetal-gazprom-neft-russian-equities-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  dropped 4.4 percent to 1,431.41
yesterday. The dollar-denominated RTS Index declined 4.5 percent
to 1,537.57, dropping for a seventh trading day.  OAO Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX): The world’s largest nickel
producer by output plans to buy back shares for the third time
in 2011. The board will consider the price of its last buyout
offer to shareholder United Co. Rusal which was $12.8 billion
for a 20 percent stake. Norilsk rose 1.6 percent to 6,603
rubles.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX): Gold futures extended a rally to a
record, topping $1,800 an ounce, on mounting demand for a haven
as global equities plunged amid escalating U.S. and European
debt woes. Polymetal rose 3.9 percent to 539.90 rubles,
advancing for the second day.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX): Oil rose from a 10-month low in
 New York  amid speculation that the  Federal Reserve  will
implement a third round of asset purchases to bolster the
economy and on an unexpected decline in U.S. crude supplies.
Gazprom Neft, the oil arm of Russia’s gas monopoly, fell 0.6
percent to 118 rubles.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
